{% extends "regular_layout.html.twig" %}
{% block title %}ContinuousPipe - for a faster development workflow{% endblock %}
{% block navigation_section_classes %}{{ parent() }} navigation-home{% endblock %}
{% block content %}
<section class="hero hero-home">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <div class="hero-content text-center">
                    <div class="continuous-pipe-logo"><i class="cp-icon-logo"></i></div>
                    <p class="intro">For a faster development workflow</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <div class="hero-content text-center">
                    <h3>Continuous Deployment for your containerized applications to Kubernetes clusters</h3>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="text-center">
                <a href="https://authenticator.continuouspipe.io/connect/github" class="btn btn-large btn-fill btn-margin-right btn-sign-in">Sign in with GitHub</a>
                <a href="{{ path('contact') }}" class="btn btn-accent btn-large">Get in touch</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
<section class="hero-strip section-padding no-icon">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="col-md-12 text-center">
            <h1 class="hero-strip__title">Why ContinuousPipe?</h1>
            <p>
                ContinuousPipe will help you solve many problems in the software development lifecycle.
                In particular, we believe that <strong>enabling a faster collaboration</strong> and <strong>reducing the cycle time</strong> is critical to delivering value.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
<section>
    <div class="container metrics__item">
        <div class="col-md-6 metrics__img">
            <img src="{{ asset('/img/branch-create-integrate.svg') }}" />
            <p class="caption text-center"><b>from days to minutes</b></p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-5 col-md-offset-1">
            <h3>No QA/staging bottleneck anymore !</h3>
            <p>Test and iterate on features minutes after a developer has created a commit or a pull-request. Gather non-technical feature before deploying to your staging environment <strong>drastically reduce your cycle time</strong>.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="container metrics__item">
        <div class="col-md-6 col-md-push-6 metrics__img">
            <img src="{{ asset('/img/technology-freedom.svg') }}" />
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6 col-md-pull-6">
            <h3>Technology freedom</h3>
            <p>By using containers, <strong>your pipeline is the same regardless the technology</strong>. You can deploy new versions of PHP, Scala or Go applications the very same way, and allow your team to use the right solution for the right problem.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="container metrics__item">
        <div class="col-md-6 metrics__img">
            <img src="{{ asset('/img/kubernetes-automated.svg') }}" />
            <p class="caption text-center"><b>from days to minutes</b></p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <h3>Automatically generated configuration for Kubernetes</h3>
            <p>Get started with container deployment at scale on Kubernetes cluster without Kubernetes configuration. From the DockerCompose configuration and ContinuousPipe's files in the code repository, <strong>your Kubernetes configuration is automatically generated</strong> !</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="container metrics__item">
        <div class="col-md-6 col-md-push-6 metrics__img">
            <img src="{{ asset('/img/this-new-feature-pull-request.png') }}" />
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6 col-md-pull-6">
            <h3>Code repository integration</h3>
            <p>Your code repository is more than that for your code. By storing all the configuration in your code repository, you also version your architecture. Deploy runtime versions changes just as if it was a feature change. <strong>Use branch names, pull-requests labels and much more to control your pipelines.</strong> <a href="https://docs.continuouspipe.io/faq/how-do-I-control-deployments-using-pr-labels/" target="_blank">Learn more about it!</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="container metrics__item">
        <div class="col-md-6 metrics__img">
            <img src="{{ asset('/img/deployed-branches.png') }}" />
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <h3>Very flexible configuration</h3>
            <p>Your configuration is in Yaml file(s) in your code repository. Compose your pipelines by ordering <a href="https://docs.continuouspipe.io/configuration/tasks/" target="_blank">tasks</a> that can build your Docker image, deploy your services, run tests or migrations, send webhooks and much more... Our API and integrations with <a href="https://docs.continuouspipe.io/configuration/notifications/#slack" target="_blank">Slack</a>, <a href="https://docs.continuouspipe.io/configuration/cloudflare-integration/" target="_blank">CloudFlare</a> and other 3rd parties will allow you to build the perfect process.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="container metrics__item">
        <div class="col-md-6 col-md-push-6 metrics__img">
            <a href="https://github.com/continuouspipe/dockerfiles" target="_blank">
                <img src="{{ asset('/img/dockerfiles.png') }}" />
            </a>
            <p class="caption text-center"><b>from days to under an hour</b></p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6 col-md-pull-6">
            <h3>We've even created images for you!</h3>
            <p>We already spent months creating <a href="https://github.com/continuouspipe/dockerfiles" target="_blank">base Docker images for many applications</a>. You don't have to, but <strong>use them to get started in minutes</strong> instead of days. You can also directly use environments deployed by ContinuousPipe as development environments!</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
{% endblock %}
